40|$|We {{find that}} {{domestic}} currency, currency corrected for foreign holdings, has a substantial share in forecast error variance decomposition of US inflation. We also find that domestic currency has higher {{share of the}} forecast error variance decomposition of US real output than any other narrow <b>monetary</b> <b>aggregate</b> we consider...|$|R
